{
  "doc_id": "1637",
  "text": "Many biological methylation reactions are catalyzed by members of the SAM-MT superfamily, which use SAM as the methyl donor to methylate substrates [CITATION_1] . Based on the substrate specificity, SAM-MTs are classified as DNA, RNA, protein, lipid, and small-molecule methyltransferases (MTs). Although SAM-MTs usually share a very low sequence similarity, several conserved motifs have been identified. The presence of motif I (CLDIGCGPG) indicates that AmJHAMT belongs to the SAM-MT superfamily, similar to previously- described JHAMT orthologs in the silkworm, mosquito, and desert locust [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
